				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Bard single pulling Feratha<a name="72686"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 05 9:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hey there.  My guild has the ability to kill Feratha, but we only have one star puller...ME!  I've spent several hours of raid time, trying to get this guy single....anyone got any tricks they can share?  For those who don't know, there are some inherent difficulties in this pull:
<br />

<br />
1.  He casts AE snare that lasts about 18 seconds, and is virtually unresistable, even with 541 all resists.
<br />

<br />
2.  He runs pretty fast.
<br />

<br />
3.  He has about 7 guards.
<br />

<br />
4.  If he and his guards lose agro anywhere from the last flight of steps upward, they will warp back.
<br />

<br />
Things I've tried:
<br />

<br />
1.  Start kazumis, hit bellow the instant before kazumis lands, run up the stairs and Fade before fera reaches me.
<br />

<br />
2.  Same thing, but try to get fera to go down the left hall (as you go down from entry level, first hall on the left), while his pets go down the right hall.  I saw a monk do this, but I haven't managed to duplicate it.
<br />

<br />
3.  Have rogues feed targets, and have chanter help try to paci his guards.  This resulted in splattage of all involved.
<br />

<br />
4.  Set up a pull relay, of people spread out between Ferathas room and the camp, people tag, and splat etc, to get him to camp, despite snare.
<br />

<br />

<br />
So, anyway, if you HAVE tried this, or better yet done it successfully, please post below. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
