				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard single pulling Feratha<a name="72705"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 30 05 12:17 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Pulling him solo is possible but to many things can go wrong, adds warp or stuff like that.  We usually bring him to camp with 1 or 2 of his guards and just mezz them.
<br />

<br />
Splitting the guards is easy but you might get a couple of splats depending if that snare lands on you. 
<br />

<br />
We usually tag team with monks. Monk or bard lull one guard and agro the rest then run down. Once the rest of the mob chase the agroer just tag the lulled mob and take him to camp. Do that a few more times and Feratha ends up solo. Also to speed things up put a mage with the pull grp since sometimes one of the pullers ends up snared and we end up having to wait for him to get out of the way before pulling again.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
