				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard single pulling Feratha<a name="72849"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 2 05 12:16 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Tan...
<br />

<br />
Do you have any monks?
<br />

<br />
We usually pull the pets first and then single Feratha at the end.
<br />

<br />
Clear the long hall past Feratha's room.  Have the Monk pull the entire room down the hallway, then pick off the pets as they return.  With a couple of enchanters you should easily be able to handle 3 pets at a time.
<br />

<br />
If no monk, YOU pull the entire room down the hall and fade.  Have the MA pull the pets as they return.  The only bad thing is if the MA gets Feratha due to shitty pathing in the area, your raid is probably dead.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
